memory usage on linux:
$ free -m

procesos que se usan 
$ps -aux

check memory usage is to read the /proc/meminfo file
$ cat /proc/meminfo

The vmstat command with the s option, lays out the memory usage statistics 
$ vmstat -s

RAM Information
$ sudo dmidecode -t 17

spacio en uso 
$ df -h


